First Fridays are back at The Los Angeles Natural History Museum (@nhmla)! This year’s theme is Fantasy & Fandoms, and it is every cosplay and science-lover’s dream! This is an opportunity for both members and non-members to enjoy an after-hours visit to the museum, while experiencing live music from @kcrw (@kcrwmusic), food trucks, costume contests, panel discussions and live, interactive exhibits with Museum Educators! It’s a scientific paradise under the stars!

Upcoming Dates:
March 3:  Witches, Wizards, and Magical Powers
April 7:  Space, Time, and Beyond
May 5:  Giant Monsters/Giant Robots
June 2:  Superheroes

A live discussion by Rebecca C. Thompson, author of Fire, Ice, and Physics; The Science of Game of Thrones-
